SIMPLE: freedom
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Freedom
<hw>Free"dom</hw> <pr>(fr⟦emac⟧"d⟦ucr⟧m)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[AS.
<ets>fre⟦oacute⟧d⟦omac⟧m</ets>; <ets>fre⟦oacute⟧</ets>free +
<ets>-dom</ets>. See <er>Free</er>, and <er>-dom</er>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>The state of being free; exemption from the power and
control of another; liberty; independence.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Made captive, yet deserving <qex>freedom</qex> more.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Privileges; franchises; immunities.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Your charter and your caty's <qex>freedom</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Exemption from necessity, in choise and action;
<as>as, the <ex>freedom</ex> of the will</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>Ease; facility; <as>as, he speaks or acts with
<ex>freedom</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <def>Frankness; openness; unreservedness.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I emboldened spake and <qex>freedom</qex> used.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>6.</sn> <def>Improper familiarity; violation of the rules of
decorum; license.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>7.</sn> <def>Generosity; liberality.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Freedom fine</b></col>, <cd>a sum paid on entry to
incorporations of trades.</cd> -- <col><b>Freedom of the city</b></col>,
<cd>the possession of the rights and privileges of a freeman of the
city; formerly often, and now occasionally, conferred on one not a
resident, as a mark of honorary distinction for public
services.</cd></cs></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- See <er>Liberty</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Freedstool</ent>⟦br⟧
